The  ministry of health has recalled two batches of Fiesta brand of condoms for failing to meet the quality standards. In a letter sent to the manufacturers of the condoms, the Pharmacy and Poisons Board says  a surveillance carried out on a sample of Fiesta Stamina and Fiesta Big Black condoms of batch number  dl1608 and pl1625  failed the freedom from holes test and thickness tests respectively . The  board has further directed cupid limited who are the  manufacturers of the condoms to  immediately recall  all the affected products and submit its report within two days  . Consumers have been advised to be on  the look out for the batch in question to avoid risks of contracting HIV and other Sexually Transmitted Diseases . Faulty condoms can also put one at risk of  having an unplanned pregnancy.  